Dictionary - "coup"
Noun
1. A quick, brilliant, and highly successful act.
  • Synonyms: triumph 2. (of Native Americans) A blow against an enemy delivered in a way that shows bravery. 3. A coup d'état.
  • Synonyms: putsch 4. (by extension) A takeover of one group by another. 5. A single roll of the wheel at roulette, or a deal in rouge et noir. 6. One of various named strategies employed by the declarer to win more tricks, such as the Bath coup.
Verb
To make a coup.
